    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This is expected behaviour, but something we might consider to change in the future. The reason is that both initial Ui State & routing are providing UI state, so we didn't want to make a complicated merge function between both and deep merges. Thus routing takes precedence if it's present. Relevant code is here:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/bae6ed2875b03a8a43c576085a19f2ceb43ba1f2/src/middleware/createRouter.ts#L50-L53\r\n\r\nI'll discuss this with the team to see what to do in this case.\r\n\r\nFor now a workaround would be to fall back to the configure widget instead of initial UI State, this will take precedence over routing.\r\n\r\n",
